  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Eprotirome is a liver selective thyroid hormone that can reduce several independent risk
      factors for cardiovascular disease, while an euthyroid state is preserved in the extrahepatic
      tissue.

      The purpose of this Phase III study is to assess the long-term efficacy and safety of
      Eprotirome in Patients with heterozygous Familial Hypercholesterolaemia who are on optimal
      standard of care.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
